Discussion

After some analysis of the data and visualization, I was able to draw certain conjectures on what allowed Leicester City FC to win the league title in 2015/16. There were definitely some limitations to data. The data was divided by each season and had match by match stats for all the games played in the season. There were also some stats that might be cardinal to our analysis but they are not included in the data set. However, from my analysis, I conclude that : First, a defensive discipline that set a high standard, making them a tough team to break down. Second, they were clinical in tight games, often playing a counter-attacking style that capitalized on small opportunities. And, lastly, we can’t ignore the element of luck, as many top teams struggled with their form that season.
